args: Mmmm! Isn't the chef's vegetable stew\nsublime, Valerio?
Helloooo? Primia to Valerio! \nCome in, Valerio!
The stew's getting cold, you know.\nYour mind has been elsewhere all day.
Our country is in peril, isn't it?
Father is trying to keep me blissfully\nunaware, but I suspect we are losing\nthe war.
Ever since it began, he won't even\nallow me to walk through the city.
I hope those children we met are okay...
Later that night, in Valerio's quarters...
*sigh* What am I doing?\nI must remain present,\nfor Her Majesty's sake!
(As she suspects, we are outmatched.\nIf we lose this war, what will become of\nthis country? Of my royal charge?)
Have I grown complacent? Lost my way?
(Is remaining at her side truly the best\nway to protect her?)
(I could be on the front lines, leading our\ntroops to victory. Would that not see\nher safe sooner?)
Was there not someone at my door?\nAm I merely jumping at shadows...?
I got the chef to make us a late-night\nsnack in hopes of cheering him up...
...But it seems that food is the\nlast thing on Valerio's mind.
(In truth, I know exactly what he wants.)
(I see the frustration on his face when our\nbloodied soldiers limp home from battle.)
Nevertheless, I can't bear the thought\nof him leading them out there.\nHe could be hurt—or worse!
But I am a princess. Prioritizing my own\nselfish desires will not protect this country.
I have to grow up. I have to be strong.
Your Majesty.\nHow might I be of service?
I have new orders for you. Effective\nimmediately, you are to resume\nleading the Azure Knights.
What? Hold on... Don't tell me\nPrincess Primia—
I said you should command the knights—\nthat you belong on the battlefield.
You must promise me one thing, Valerio.
Promise that you will return home safely,\nand be my royal knight once more.
I swear it, Your Highness.\nI will return to your side hale and whole!
You shall depart for the front immediately,\nand rejoin your knights there.
Fight well, Valerio.\nProtect this land as only you can.
We've lost too many men.\nWhat are we supposed to do now?
What choice do we have?\nIf we withdraw at this point, \nour kingdom will be no more.
But... Without our captain,\ncan we really drive them back?
I do believe I forbade idle chatter\non the battlefield, soldier!
I'm here at His Majesty's behest.\nI've been assigned command of the\nAzure Knights, effective immediately.
Thank the Heavens! With you\nleading us again, we might truly\nwin the day!

Listen well, all of you.
The only way we go home alive is
to fight as if we're as good as dead.
Find strength in your desperation!
We will protect Mentzara,\nno matter the cost!
What the hell?! They're moving like\nmen possessed!
Behind me, men! Remember what your\nfallen comrades fought and died for!\nDo not let their sacrifices be in vain!
(With this sword, I will claim victory.\nAnd then I will honor my promise.\nI WILL protect you, my princess!)
Valerio's heroism reinvigorated the Mentzaran\narmy. Little by little, the tide of war turned.
Meanwhile, as the princess awaited\nher knight's return at the castle...
I'm finished. You can clear the plates.
Your Highness? You've barely touched\nyour food. Was it not to your taste?
I don't know... It looked appetizing, but...\nIt... Nghhh...
